  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe validator client must `subscribe` its validators to future slots in order to determine if it is an aggregator of attestations or not. Currently we sign with the fork_version of the current head. \r\n\r\nIt's possible that the fork version changes by the time we are supposed to aggregate. The validator client should detect fork-version changes and update it's duties accordingly. A duties update, should trigger new subscriptions and the beacon node should handle obsolete aggregates via cache pruning (this should already be handled). \r\n",
